===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*h₂weg-|*-tus}}
From {{inh|en|enm|waste}}, {{m|enm|wast||stature, waist}}, from {{der|en|ang|wǣst}}, {{m|ang|*wǣxt}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*wahstuz||growth, development, stature, build}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₂weg-|*h₂weg-s-|to multiply, increase}}. Cognate with {{cog|gmh|wahst||growth}}, {{cog|da|vækst||growth}}, {{cog|sv|växt||growth, development, size}}, {{cog|is|vöxtur||growth}}, {{cog|got|𐍅𐌰𐌷𐍃𐍄𐌿𐍃||growth}}. Related to {{cog|ang|weaxan||to grow, increase}}. More at {{l|en|wax}}.

